body:
When visiting apptree, this one came up.  Easy to repro.

1. Set a breakpoint.
2. When paused, evaluate an expression.
3. Exception is thrown.

To get back to a happy state we need to restart the analysis server.



Analyzer Feedback from IntelliJ

# Version information

- `IDEA 183.2940.10`
- `2.1.0-edge.4cf2d3990bac1f1df2f524899e1560a3683f3133`
- `IU-183.2940.10, JRE 1.8.0_151-b12x64 Oracle Corporation, OS Mac OS X(x86_64) v10.13.6, screens 1680x1050  Retina`

# Exception

comment_data.body:
I've seen this myself a couple times.
Unfortunately I didn't have time to implement a proper fix yet.

As another point of reference: you can get back to a happy place by editing and re-saving the file.

> Unfortunately I didn't have time to implement a proper fix yet.

Is this a fix here or in the dart plugin?

It should be fixed in Analysis Server.
API and the Dart plugin are fine.
OK, great.  Should I move this to the SDK?
This issue was moved to dart-lang/sdk#34646

milestone.title: On Deck

title: Evaluating an expression @ a breakpoint causes analysis to fall down.
